Installation of Kubectl - 

Root -
sudo su

Update System Packages -
sudo apt-get update

Install Required Dependencies -
sudo apt-get install -y apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl gnupg

Add Kubernetes Signing Key -
curl -fsSL https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.35/deb/Release.key | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg

Give permission -
sudo chmod 644 /etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg

Add Kubernetes Repository -
echo 'deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg] https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.35/deb/ /' | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list

Set permission -
sudo chmod 644 /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list

Install kubectl -

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y kubectl        

Verify Installation -

kubectl version --client





Installation of Miniqube:

Download Minikube - 
curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube_latest_amd64.deb 

Install Minikube -
sudo dpkg -i minikube_latest_amd64.deb

Verify installation -
minikube version

Start Minikube Cluster -
minikube start

Check Cluster Status -
minikube status


You should see:
     host: Running
     kubelet: Running
     apiserver: Running

Check Kubernetes Nodes -
kubectl get nodes






Deploy Nginx Pod:

Create Pod Configuration File -
nano pod.yaml

Paste this:

apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: nginx
spec:
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx:1.14.2
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80

Save:
CTRL + X → Y → Enter


Create pod -
kubectl create -f pod.yaml

Check pod status -
kubectl get pods -o wide

Wait until status shows:
Running
(Now you’ll see the pod IP)

Test Pod Inside Minikube:

Login to Minikube VM -
minikube ssh

Access Nginx Using Pod IP:

Inside Minikube -
curl <pod-ip>

Exit - 
exit

What You Achieved -

✅ Installed kubectl
✅ Installed Minikube
✅ Started Kubernetes cluster
✅ Created Nginx Pod
✅ Verified pod running
✅Accessed application
